I'm not thrilled about the idea,

87
00:03:56,346 --> 00:03:59,493
but he has every right
to date someone else.

88
00:03:59,505 --> 00:04:01,453
That's very mature.

89
00:04:01,465 --> 00:04:03,122
Why are you holding the phone?

90
00:04:03,136 --> 00:04:04,843
Oh, shoot.

91
00:04:06,025 --> 00:04:08,693
That's hilarious, Mom.

92
00:04:08,705 --> 00:04:10,833
Didn't even notice.

93
00:04:12,368 --> 00:04:15,022
Hey, dude, by the way,
I really like that suit.

94
00:04:15,035 --> 00:04:17,220
Tell me about the fabric.
Is it foreign or something?

95
00:04:17,235 --> 00:04:20,161
Wow. It is foreign.
I'm impressed, Ted.

96
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:21,620
- It's Moroccan, actually.
- Whoa.

97
00:04:21,637 --> 00:04:24,132
I got a call for Swarley.

98
00:04:24,145 --> 00:04:26,282
Is there a Swarley here?

99
00:04:26,296 --> 00:04:28,342
You weren't interested in
my suit at all, were you?

100
00:04:28,355 --> 00:04:30,512
- Hmm?
- Swarley!

101
00:04:31,848 --> 00:04:34,843
Yeah, I know he's there.
It's really important.

102
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:36,350
Could you ask again?

103
00:04:36,368 --> 00:04:38,441
Important call for Swarley!

104
00:04:38,456 --> 00:04:40,912
Geez,  can't you hear him, Swarley?
There's a call for you.

105
00:04:40,927 --> 00:04:43,413
Stop calling me that.

106
00:04:43,427 --> 00:04:45,961
Uh...  Hey, I'd like you guys
to officially meet Chloe.

107
00:04:45,976 --> 00:04:46,962
- Hi.
- Hi.

108
00:04:46,978 --> 00:04:47,863
Hi.

109
00:04:47,877 --> 00:04:49,393
It's nice to meet you guys.

110
00:04:49,407 --> 00:04:51,713
- I'll be right back.
- It's right back there.

111
00:04:55,918 --> 00:04:58,381
Right? Right? She's hot!

112
00:04:58,398 --> 00:04:59,860
And she likes me?

113
00:04:59,878 --> 00:05:03,160
She likes Italian food.
I also like Italian food.

114
00:05:03,177 --> 00:05:06,593
She likes Billy Joel.
I also like... music.

115
00:05:06,605 --> 00:05:09,553
And I think we're
going to go out again.

116
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:12,130
- Dude, you gotta ditch her.
- Obviously.

117
00:05:12,596 --> 00:05:13,523
Why?

118
00:05:13,538 --> 00:05:14,833
She's got the crazy eyes.

119
00:05:14,847 --> 00:05:16,791
Dude. The eyes.

120
00:05:16,806 --> 00:05:18,492
They're crazy.

121
00:05:18,508 --> 00:05:20,502
What are you guys talking about,
the crazy eyes?

122
00:05:20,517 --> 00:05:24,583
It's a well-documented condition
of the pupils, or pupi.

123
00:05:24,597 --> 00:05:25,860
No. Just pupils.

124
00:05:25,876 --> 00:05:29,343
It's an indicator of
future mental instability.

125
00:05:29,356 --> 00:05:32,100
She does not have
the crazy eyes.

126
00:05:32,116 --> 00:05:33,822
You just can't see it
because you're afflicted

127
00:05:33,855 --> 00:05:36,731
with "haven't been laid
in a while" blindness.

128
00:05:36,747 --> 00:05:38,600
She was too far away
in the coffee place,

129
00:05:38,616 --> 00:05:41,523
but when I saw her
up close just now...

130
00:05:41,548 --> 00:05:43,523
Hey, I'd like you guys to
officially meet Chloe.

131
00:05:43,537 --> 00:05:44,623
- Hi.
- Hi.

132
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:45,582
Hi.

133
00:05:45,598 --> 00:05:47,362
It's nice to meet you guys.

134
00:05:52,768 --> 00:05:54,551
You guys,
I'm not going to stop dating Chloe

135
00:05:54,566 --> 00:05:57,040
just because you think
she has the crazy eyes.

136
00:05:57,056 --> 00:05:59,100
You can keep going out with her,
but you're gonna regret it.

137
00:05:59,136 --> 00:06:01,560
One time,
I met a girl at this very bar.

138
00:06:01,575 --> 00:06:04,651
I saw that she had
the crazy eyes...

139
00:06:06,558 --> 00:06:07,830
...but I ignored it.

140
00:06:07,845 --> 00:06:10,183
And then, sure enough.

141
00:06:10,846 --> 00:06:12,922
Barney, can I ask
you a question?

142
00:06:12,935 --> 00:06:14,413
Anything.

143
00:06:14,766 --> 00:06:17,430
Would you like to
have a threesome?

144
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:19,086
Of course.

145
00:06:19,092 --> 00:06:21,859
Great. It'll be you,
me and Mr. Weasels.

146
00:06:24,099 --> 00:06:25,703
So, did you do it?

147
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:28,211
No. It ended up
being just a twosome

148
00:06:28,228 --> 00:06:30,580
with the third one
watching from a chair.

149
00:06:31,015 --> 00:06:32,621
Which one were you?

150
00:06:33,446 --> 00:06:35,200
I'd rather not say.

151
00:06:35,518 --> 00:06:38,062
Look, there was a time I didn't
believe in the crazy eyes either,

152
00:06:38,096 --> 00:06:40,010
and then I met Jeanine.

153
00:06:40,075 --> 00:06:42,773
She had serious crazy eyes.

154
00:06:43,225 --> 00:06:46,663
I told myself I was 
just imagining it, but then...

155
00:06:46,677 --> 00:06:48,440
So, should we go get a drink?

156
00:06:48,456 --> 00:06:50,860
As long as it's in
your apartment.

157
00:06:52,127 --> 00:06:53,180
Whoa, I'm sorry.

158
00:06:53,195 --> 00:06:58,100
Watch! Where! You're! Going!

159
00:06:59,995 --> 00:07:02,192
So, where do you live?

160
00:07:03,026 --> 00:07:05,832
You guys, Chloe is not 
gonna do any of that stuff.

161
00:07:05,847 --> 00:07:07,642
She's a nice girl
from Nebraska.

162
00:07:07,656 --> 00:07:08,851
She's not crazy.

163
00:07:08,866 --> 00:07:11,021
She's... she's awesome.

164
00:07:11,037 --> 00:07:13,243
But you can't avoid
the crazy eyes forever.

165
00:07:13,256 --> 00:07:16,180
Sooner or later, the crazy 
comes bubbling to the surface.

166
00:07:16,197 --> 00:07:16,980
Hello?

167
00:07:16,995 --> 00:07:18,621
Marshall, it's Chloe.

168
00:07:18,637 --> 00:07:21,233
Are you the one who's
called me like nine times?

169
00:07:21,245 --> 00:07:23,340
Yeah. Could you come get me?

170
00:07:23,355 --> 00:07:25,801
I'm in the middle
of taking a test.

171
00:07:25,816 --> 00:07:27,772
Please.  I'm so scared.

172
00:07:28,017 --> 00:07:29,430
Well, what's going on?

173
00:07:29,448 --> 00:07:31,463
This weird midget guy
started following me

174
00:07:31,478 --> 00:07:32,650
and he was screaming at me

175
00:07:32,665 --> 00:07:34,891
and he had a limp and
a big hump on his back

176
00:07:34,906 --> 00:07:36,300
and the police
didn't believe me

177
00:07:36,316 --> 00:07:39,150
and I almost got trampled
by a horse and...

178
00:07:39,165 --> 00:07:42,041
God I must sound totally
crazy to you right now.

179
00:07:42,656 --> 00:07:45,010
No. Pfft.

180
00:07:45,025 --> 00:07:46,301
Not at all.

181
00:07:46,928 --> 00:07:48,650
So, she's needy crazy.

182
00:07:48,668 --> 00:07:50,440
That's one of the worst kinds.

183
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:51,760
I've had one of those.

184
00:07:51,776 --> 00:07:53,461
Makes up stories
to get attention.

185
00:07:53,476 --> 00:07:56,662
Went out with her for three weeks--
her dad died twice.

186
00:07:56,677 --> 00:07:59,511
Guys, she was really
freaked out, okay?

187
00:07:59,526 --> 00:08:01,083
Maybe the story is true.

188
00:08:01,095 --> 00:08:03,833
What in the world would make
you believe that's a true story?

189
00:08:03,845 --> 00:08:06,370
She's really hot.

190
00:08:06,445 --> 00:08:08,690
They always are.

191
00:08:09,966 --> 00:08:11,600
- You all done with that, Ted?
- Yeah.

192
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:14,313
Ned. I told you
to call him Ned.

193
00:08:14,465 --> 00:08:16,322
That's just sad.

194
00:08:16,338 --> 00:08:18,102
Sorry, Swarley.

195
00:08:19,357 --> 00:08:21,831
So, do just you
and Ted live here

196
00:08:21,847 --> 00:08:23,610
or does Swarley live here, too?

197
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:26,553
Nah. Swarley has his own place.

198
00:08:29,916 --> 00:08:30,941
What was that?

199
00:08:30,958 --> 00:08:32,672
Oh, I, uh, dropped my keys.

200
00:08:34,836 --> 00:08:36,562
So, here you go.

201
00:08:36,576 --> 00:08:39,010
Two pumpkin beers.

202
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:41,881
I was joking.
They're regular beers.

203
00:08:44,736 --> 00:08:46,403
What is that?

204
00:08:53,306 --> 00:08:55,191
This picture is broken.

205
00:08:55,206 --> 00:08:58,103
Oh. That's too bad.

206
00:08:58,116 --> 00:08:59,920
Is that Lily?

207
00:08:59,938 --> 00:09:02,221
Is  that the girl you
were going to marry?

208
00:09:02,238 --> 00:09:04,393
Yeah. Is that what
that sound was?

209
00:09:04,405 --> 00:09:06,633
Did you just smash this?

210
00:09:06,648 --> 00:09:07,932
No.

211
00:09:07,946 --> 00:09:10,220
Why would I do that?

212
00:09:11,238 --> 00:09:13,562
Let me look into your eyes.

213
00:09:14,078 --> 00:09:15,730
Okay.

214
00:09:18,708 --> 00:09:21,300
I had a really
nice time tonight.

215
00:09:21,316 --> 00:09:23,592
Yeah, me, too. Stop blinking.

216
00:09:23,925 --> 00:09:27,373
I like your eyes a lot, too.

217
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:30,642
Stop!

218
00:09:34,207 --> 00:09:36,893
Hi. I'm Lily.

219
00:09:40,176 --> 00:09:42,122
Stop!

220
00:09:42,137 --> 00:09:44,223
Now, kids,
I know Lily hiding in the apartment

221
00:09:44,235 --> 00:09:47,522
while Marshall was on a date with
another girl seems pretty crazy,

222
00:09:47,536 --> 00:09:49,880
but when you hear her
side of the story,

223
00:09:49,896 --> 00:09:51,950
well, it's still pretty crazy.

224
00:09:52,626 --> 00:09:54,182
What's up Swarlz?

225
00:09:54,198 --> 00:09:56,400
No. Okay? No. No more.

226
00:09:56,416 --> 00:09:58,470
I will not let this 
become a thing. It's over.

227
00:09:58,488 --> 00:10:00,450
No more Swarley. No Swarlz.

228
00:10:00,465 --> 00:10:02,941
No more Swar-lay.

229
00:10:02,956 --> 00:10:05,922
No  more Swar...
wait for it... ley.

230
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:08,510
No more Bob Swarley, mon.

231
00:10:08,526 --> 00:10:11,470
No more. No! It's over.

232
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:13,061
Do you understand?

233
00:10:13,075 --> 00:10:13,901
- Yes.
- Yes.

234
00:10:13,916 --> 00:10:15,412
Thank you.

235
00:10:18,135 --> 00:10:19,000
Nice.

236
00:10:19,017 --> 00:10:21,192
- Why didn't you call me?
- Was I supposed to call you?

237
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,462
Yes, about the whole Marshall-
dating-another-girl thing.

238
00:10:24,475 --> 00:10:25,590
You said you were fine with it.

239
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:28,623
Yeah, in front of Ted,
but then I shot you a look.

240
00:10:28,636 --> 00:10:30,972
- What look?
- This.

241
00:10:32,806 --> 00:10:34,510
